showed up at the awards?

05:23.090 --> 05:23.991
Yeah.

05:24.091 --> 05:25.025
Why would she do that?

05:25.125 --> 05:26.527
Because she's his wife,

05:26.627 --> 05:28.796
and she wants to share
his life with him?

05:28.896 --> 05:31.399
I guess I never really
thought about his wife.

05:31.499 --> 05:33.000
That was the great part.

05:33.100 --> 05:34.402
She's in Sweden.

05:34.502 --> 05:36.203
Yeah, no one ever
thinks about the wife.

05:36.303 --> 05:38.071
All the sacrifices
she's made,

05:38.171 --> 05:40.541
all the dinners she's cooked,
all the toilets she's cleaned.

05:40.641 --> 05:42.209
If this woman finds out
about the affair,

05:42.309 --> 05:43.644
she's gonna be devastated.

05:43.744 --> 05:45.479
Girls in their 20s
don't think about that.

05:45.579 --> 05:47.748
"Girls in their 20s"?

05:47.848 --> 05:49.983
You're in your 20s.

05:50.083 --> 05:51.552
Yeah, but I'm very mature.

05:51.652 --> 05:53.421
I spent a lot of years
meditating.

05:53.487 --> 05:55.489
I just don't get it.

05:55.589 --> 05:57.190
What's in this for you?

05:57.290 --> 05:59.159
What?
Are you kidding me?

05:59.259 --> 06:01.128
He's this brilliant writer

06:01.228 --> 06:02.996
who happens to be
amazing in bed.

06:03.096 --> 06:04.832
I'm not gonna
pass that up.

06:04.932 --> 06:08.168
And by the way,
isn't Anton's wife his problem?

06:08.268 --> 06:10.137
Yeah, but who's
problem is Thad?

06:10.237 --> 06:12.005
If Thad and I
are gonna be together,

06:12.105 --> 06:14.207
I'm probably gonna be
happy I had the affair.

06:14.307 --> 06:16.076
I don't want to be
one of those women

06:16.176 --> 06:18.446
who wakes up at 40 and realizes
she forgot to have a life.

06:18.479 --> 06:19.847
Okay, Kelsey,

06:19.947 --> 06:22.349
I'm your friend,
but I got to tell you,

06:22.450 --> 06:25.085
your adventure with Bjornberg
has collateral damage.

06:25.185 --> 06:26.520
[cell phone chimes]

06:26.620 --> 06:29.356
And I got to go pick her up
at the airport.

06:39.667 --> 06:41.234
Thank you so much
for meeting me.

06:41.334 --> 06:44.037
Please, let me
treat you to lunch.

06:44.137 --> 06:46.239
I can't. I have to get
back to the office.

06:46.339 --> 06:48.542
There's, like, a million errands
to do before the awards tonight.

06:48.642 --> 06:51.078
You must take 20 minutes
for a bite to eat.

06:51.178 --> 06:52.846
I insist.
Come.

06:52.946 --> 06:54.114
Okay.

06:55.716 --> 06:57.585
And the linguini
with clam sauce for you.

06:57.685 --> 06:58.586
Thank you.

06:58.686 --> 06:59.687
More jasmine iced tea?

06:59.787 --> 07:02.189
Uh, please.

07:02.289 --> 07:03.657
This is heaven.

07:03.757 --> 07:06.159
Well, you assistants--
you take care of everyone.

07:06.259 --> 07:08.562
You deserve to be taken
care of once in a while.

07:08.662 --> 07:10.263
Not everyone
thinks that way.

07:10.363 --> 07:12.099
Well, I remember very well

07:12.199 --> 07:14.067
what it's like to have
these jobs in your 20s.

07:16.103 --> 07:18.171
You're in your 20s,
Liza, yes?

07:18.271 --> 07:20.373
Yes, I'm 26.

07:20.508 --> 07:22.676
You're so lovely.

07:22.776 --> 07:26.179
Your eyes--they're
very much like doe eyes.

07:26.279 --> 07:27.915
Has anyone ever
said that to you before?

07:28.015 --> 07:30.518
Maybe.

07:30.618 --> 07:32.853
My husband said you've been
showing him such hospitality

07:32.953 --> 07:34.522
while he's been here
in New York.

07:34.555 --> 07:37.390
The whole company
is so happy to have him.

07:37.525 --> 07:39.026
My husband--

07:39.126 --> 07:41.228
he started writing
his new novel.

07:41.328 --> 07:43.430
He sends me
all the pages.

07:43.531 --> 07:44.532
Wow, that's exciting.

07:44.565 --> 07:45.866
Yes, it is.

07:45.966 --> 07:47.300
And, of course,
you know that

07:47.400 --> 07:49.402
Anton always writes
from his real experiences.

07:49.537 --> 07:53.406
And this is about his
experiences here in New York.

07:53.541 --> 07:55.042
Would you like me
to read you some?

07:55.142 --> 07:56.544
Sure.

07:59.880 --> 08:04.351
[speaking in Swedish]

08:04.451 --> 08:06.453
I'm so sorry.
I don't speak Swedish.

08:06.554 --> 08:09.923
[shouting in Swedish]

08:14.995 --> 08:16.096
What--what--
what's going on?

08:16.196 --> 08:17.931
Don't pretend
you don't know!

08:18.031 --> 08:19.867
He writes about you.

08:19.967 --> 08:21.569
His 26-year-old mistress

08:21.635 --> 08:24.371
who works as an assistant
in a publishing house!

08:24.471 --> 08:25.706
He wrote about that?

08:25.806 --> 08:26.740
So you admit it?

08:26.840 --> 08:28.108
No, no, no--
it's not me.

08:28.208 --> 08:29.577
Oh, it's not you,
with the doe eyes?

08:29.643 --> 08:33.480
[speaking in Swedish]

08:33.581 --> 08:34.748
A what?

08:34.847 --> 08:37.751
A vagina as soft
as a walrus' fold.

08:37.851 --> 08:41.722
[shouting in Swedish]

08:41.822 --> 08:42.756
You!

08:42.856 --> 08:44.958
You stay away
from my husband!

08:54.067 --> 08:56.169
I just had lunch
with Bjornberg's wife.

08:56.269 --> 08:57.805
Is she pretty?

08:57.905 --> 08:59.439
- Not when she's hitting me.
- What?

08:59.607 --> 09:01.208
She knows he's having
an affair.

09:01.308 --> 09:03.744
She thinks I'm the one
he's sleeping with.

09:03.844 --> 09:05.613
What would make her
think that?

09:05.679 --> 09:06.947
He wrote about it
in his new book.

09:07.047 --> 09:09.216
He said his mistress
has doe eyes

09:09.316 --> 09:11.852
and a vagina as soft
as a walrus' fold.

09:11.952 --> 09:14.722
Okay, something must have
gotten lost in translation.

09:14.822 --> 09:17.457
Kelsey, this is serious.

09:17.625 --> 09:19.927
I know, I know.

09:20.027 --> 09:21.428
I have to break things off
with Anton.

09:21.528 --> 09:22.630
But I can't right now.

09:22.730 --> 09:24.297
