is play video games.

11:29.489 --> 11:31.391
Need some wine?

11:31.491 --> 11:32.392
Thank you.

11:32.492 --> 11:34.061
Want some parmigiano?

11:34.161 --> 11:36.396
- Prosciutto.
- Yes.

11:36.496 --> 11:38.465
And can we put on our sweats
and watch Downton Abbey?

11:38.565 --> 11:40.067
Absolutely.

11:40.167 --> 11:41.902
It'll be like having
a 40-year-old time-out.

11:42.002 --> 11:43.136
Should I break out
the slanket?

11:43.236 --> 11:44.137
I love you.

11:44.237 --> 11:45.438
[cell phone buzzing]

11:45.538 --> 11:47.540
Mm, getting a call?

11:47.640 --> 11:50.477
- Oh, no.
- What?

11:50.577 --> 11:52.379
Hello?

11:52.479 --> 11:54.247
Charles' babysitter didn't show,
so I volunteered you.

11:54.347 --> 11:56.049
Uh, I'm already
back in Brooklyn.

11:56.149 --> 11:58.285
If only there were some sort
of underground train system

11:58.385 --> 12:00.420
that could get you to the upper
West side in 30 minutes,

12:00.520 --> 12:02.322
which is when
he's expecting you.

12:02.422 --> 12:04.657
Is this already
a done deal?

12:04.792 --> 12:06.293
I'm texting you
the address right now.

12:06.393 --> 12:07.895
Leave immediately.

12:07.995 --> 12:09.362
What?

12:09.462 --> 12:10.998
I have to go babysit
my boss' boss' kids.

12:11.098 --> 12:11.999
- Now?
- Yup.

12:12.099 --> 12:13.801
Back to 26.

12:13.901 --> 12:15.936
Oh, you poor thing.
Here, chug that.

12:22.475 --> 12:23.944
(Charles)
Thank you for coming, Liza.

12:24.044 --> 12:25.378
You are really
saving the day.

12:25.478 --> 12:28.081
Oh, well,
it's no problem.

12:28.181 --> 12:30.383
Hi.
I'm Liza.

12:30.483 --> 12:33.353
This is Bianca.
That's Nicole.

12:33.453 --> 12:35.388
Say hi.
Don't be shy.

12:37.290 --> 12:39.893
I used to babysit
a girl who was very shy.

12:39.993 --> 12:41.361
What was her name?

12:41.461 --> 12:42.930
Kaitlyn.

12:43.030 --> 12:44.364
And you know what
Kaitlyn loved?

12:44.464 --> 12:45.365
What?

12:45.465 --> 12:46.599
Polly Pockets.

12:46.699 --> 12:48.535
So do I!

12:48.635 --> 12:50.838
It's too bad we don't have any
here that we could play with.

12:50.904 --> 12:52.405
We do!

12:52.505 --> 12:54.041
I have Polly, Lea,
Chrissy, Lila, and Shani.

12:54.141 --> 12:56.309
- Come to my playroom!
- No, come to my playroom.

12:56.409 --> 12:58.045
What, you have two
playrooms?

12:58.145 --> 12:59.579
And a media room
and a library.

12:59.679 --> 13:01.148
- Wow.
- Come on!

13:01.248 --> 13:03.116
- Have fun.
- You too.

13:03.216 --> 13:04.417
Be good.

13:08.856 --> 13:11.691
It's so difficult being
married to a renowned author.

13:11.859 --> 13:14.862
Women literally throw
themselves at Anton.

13:14.962 --> 13:17.030
They think baiting
a literary giant

13:17.130 --> 13:19.867
will give meaning to their
miserable little lives.

13:19.900 --> 13:22.269
Well, I suppose
some of the--

13:22.369 --> 13:24.872
Those little groupies?
They're disgusting.

13:24.972 --> 13:27.374
And you know the women
I'm talking about, yes?

13:27.474 --> 13:30.043
Yes, yes, yes.

13:30.143 --> 13:32.579
Yes, I do.
Excuse me.

13:35.682 --> 13:37.584
I can't believe
you wrote about our affair

13:37.684 --> 13:39.119
and showed your wife.

13:39.219 --> 13:41.955
It was vague.
Could be anyone your age.

13:42.055 --> 13:44.157
Oh, anyone in publishing

13:44.257 --> 13:47.394
who has doe eyes
and a walrus vagina?

13:47.494 --> 13:49.496
What the hell
does that even mean?

13:49.596 --> 13:51.598
Have you ever touched
a walrus fold?

13:51.698 --> 13:54.167
When would I ever
do that?

13:54.267 --> 13:57.270
Well, then you cannot
understand.

13:57.370 --> 13:59.973
It is the highest
compliment in my country.

14:04.011 --> 14:05.913
Oh, no!
Oh, no!

14:05.979 --> 14:07.314
The zombies are closing in!

14:07.414 --> 14:08.916
What am I gonna do?

14:09.016 --> 14:09.917
Oh, no!
Oh--

14:10.017 --> 14:10.984
[cell phone chimes]

14:11.084 --> 14:12.019
Freeze!

14:14.654 --> 14:16.589
I got to text
the sheriff.

14:27.567 --> 14:28.635
Okay.

14:28.735 --> 14:31.471
Oh, no! Oh, no!
Ow, my brains!

14:31.571 --> 14:34.474
(man)
This year's PEN
social justice award

14:34.574 --> 14:36.743
goes to Alex Minnick.

14:36.843 --> 14:38.745
[applause]

14:38.845 --> 14:41.781
[both speaking in Swedish]

14:57.364 --> 14:58.798
Long line at the bar.

14:58.966 --> 15:00.968
Thought I'd bring you
another scotch just in case.

15:01.034 --> 15:02.169
Well, thank you.

15:02.269 --> 15:04.104
Oh.

15:04.204 --> 15:06.739
So, how are you
holding up?

15:06.839 --> 15:08.575
Oh, you know.

15:08.675 --> 15:09.842
Day by day.

15:09.977 --> 15:11.478
Divorce is tough.

15:11.578 --> 15:13.613
Are you divorced?

15:13.713 --> 15:15.015
Yes, yes.

15:15.115 --> 15:16.516
I was married briefly
in my 20s.

15:16.616 --> 15:18.518
Everyone kept asking,
"What happened?"

15:18.618 --> 15:20.287
Like it's so easy
to explain.

15:20.387 --> 15:22.855
Well, it's, uh,
easy for me to explain.

15:22.990 --> 15:24.591
My wife left me
for another man.

15:24.691 --> 15:26.526
So did my husband.

15:26.626 --> 15:29.329
[cell phone chimes]

15:29.429 --> 15:31.864
It's from Liza.

15:31.999 --> 15:33.100
I asked her to check in
with me.

15:33.200 --> 15:34.601
(Liza)
Oh...

15:34.701 --> 15:36.369
Brains!

15:36.469 --> 15:38.005
Oh, no!

15:38.105 --> 15:40.707
She is just fantastic
with kids.

15:40.807 --> 15:42.042
I love kids too.

15:42.142 --> 15:45.012
Some people
find them annoying,

15:45.112 --> 15:46.679
but I-I just love them.

15:46.779 --> 15:48.481
(man)
Welcome back,
ladies and gentlemen.

15:48.581 --> 15:51.718
Looks like Bjornberg
is up next.

15:51.818 --> 15:53.153
Anton, stop it.

15:53.253 --> 15:55.222
Your wife is right there.

15:55.322 --> 15:56.323
[speaking indistinctly]

15:56.423 --> 15:57.524
It's brilliant.

15:57.624 --> 16:01.128
No, it's--it's terrible.

16:01.228 --> 16:04.031
Listen, this whole thing--

16:04.131 --> 16:06.299
I've loved our time
together, okay,

16:06.399 --> 16:07.900
but it needs to end.

16:08.035 --> 16:09.902
I mean it.

16:10.037 --> 16:11.404
[clears throat]

16:14.407 --> 16:15.675
[gasps]

16:15.775 --> 16:17.110
This is how I feel
when you say that.

16:17.210 --> 16:18.111
What are you doing?

16:18.211 --> 16:19.546
I will not agree to this.

16:19.646 --> 16:21.714
Stop.
God, you're bleeding.

16:21.814 --> 16:23.616
(man)
And this year's PEN
Scandinavian prize

16:23.716 --> 16:26.286
goes to Anton Bjornberg.

16:26.386 --> 16:28.688
I refuse to lose you.

16:28.788 --> 16:30.457
Okay, okay.
You won't have to.

16:30.557 --> 16:31.558
Just go. Go.

16:31.658 --> 16:33.593
[applause]

16:45.672 --> 16:47.074
I don't think
we've officially met.

16:47.140 --> 16:49.176
I'm Kelsey Peters.
I'm Anton's editor.

16:49.276 --> 16:52.179
Oh.
Nice to meet you, Kelsey.

16:52.279 --> 16:54.314
I'm the one sleeping
with your husband.

16:54.414 --> 16:55.582
Excuse me?

16:55.682 --> 16:57.384
It's not Liza.

16:57.484 --> 16:59.419
I am the walrus.

17:03.856 --> 17:05.291
Hello?

17:09.929 --> 17:10.829
Are they asleep?

17:10.930 --> 17:11.830
Oh, yeah.
Hours ago.

17:11.931 --> 17:12.832
How was it?

17:12.932 --> 17:14.267
Everything was great.

17:14.367 --> 17:17.604
Except Kelsey Peters
left rather abruptly.

17:17.704 --> 17:20.406
Yeah, she texted me.
She was sick.

17:20.507 --> 17:22.242
How did everything
go here?

17:22.342 --> 17:23.510
Oh, it was great.

17:23.609 --> 17:25.978
You didn't do
the windows, did you?

17:26.113 --> 17:29.449
Uh, no, that's
"monster go away" spray.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.251
[laughs]

17:31.351 --> 17:32.785
Can I
offer you a drink?

17:32.885 --> 17:35.788
Sure. I'll have
what you're having.

17:35.888 --> 17:37.624
Uh--

17:37.724 --> 17:41.161
Okay.
Thank you.

17:41.261 --> 17:43.330
The girls--they were
just angels tonight.

17:43.430 --> 17:44.931
I am glad to hear that.

17:45.031 --> 17:46.266
Please.

17:46.366 --> 17:48.768
This divorce has been
rough on them,

17:48.868 --> 17:50.903
and they can act out.

17:51.003 --> 17:52.672
Well, you must be doing
something right.

17:52.772 --> 17:54.674
I don't know,
their mother's in California,

17:54.774 --> 17:57.043
and the girls haven't
seen her for months.

17:57.144 --> 17:59.212
Yeah, Nicole told me.
It's rough.

17:59.312 --> 18:01.914
Yeah, it's a mess.

18:02.014 --> 18:03.650
Mm, it's okay.

18:03.750 --> 18:06.018
Messes make people
interesting.

18:06.153 --> 18:08.321
They do?

18:08.421 --> 18:10.590
Yes.
The messier, the better.

18:10.690 --> 18:12.825
Name any great artist.

18:12.925 --> 18:15.162
Uh, Beethoven.

18:15.262 --> 18:17.029
Alcoholic father.

18:17.164 --> 18:19.065
Kurt Vonnegut.

18:20.967 --> 18:22.702
Searching.
Okay, keep going.

18:22.802 --> 18:23.836
Jonathan Franzen.

18:23.936 --> 18:25.805
Oh, messy divorce.

18:25.905 --> 18:26.806
Woody Allen.

18:26.906 --> 18:28.175
[scoffs]
Please.

18:28.241 --> 18:29.709
[laughs]

18:29.809 --> 18:33.180
Vonnegut--
mom committed suicide. Boom.

18:33.246 --> 18:36.849
So now we're taking pleasure
in other peoples' misery?

18:36.949 --> 18:39.186
No, we're taking solace
in other peoples' misery,

18:39.286 --> 18:43.456
and we should do it frequently
in order to maintain our sanity.

18:43.556 --> 18:45.458
You sure you're 26?

18:45.558 --> 18:47.660
[laughs]

18:47.760 --> 18:49.095
[cell phone chimes]

18:52.665 --> 18:54.567
Oh, a friend's
walking me home.

18:54.667 --> 18:57.670
Oh, I was gonna call you a car,
but that's good.

18:57.770 --> 18:59.872
So I'll--I'll see you
at the office?

18:59.972 --> 19:00.973
Yeah.

19:01.208 --> 19:03.476
Maybe you can
babysit again.

19:03.576 --> 19:07.380
Yeah, just let me know.

19:07.480 --> 19:08.981
Yeah, you don't want me
to keep you here

19:09.081 --> 19:10.983
when you have
a young man waiting.

19:11.083 --> 19:13.520
Well, how do you know
it's a young man?

19:15.755 --> 19:17.257
Isn't it?

19:19.226 --> 19:22.128
Uh, yeah, it is.

19:25.565 --> 19:27.600
Okay. Sorry.
Good night.

19:27.700 --> 19:29.602
Good night.

19:31.838 --> 19:34.073
Wait.

19:34.241 --> 19:36.643
I, uh,

19:36.743 --> 19:39.246
forgot to, uh, pay you.

19:42.982 --> 19:44.817
Thank you.

19:44.917 --> 19:46.553
Thank you.

19:46.653 --> 19:48.355
I'll see you at work.

19:48.455 --> 19:50.257
You got it.

19:51.958 --> 19:53.393
Good night.

20:01.634 --> 20:03.403
You didn't have
to come get me.

20:03.503 --> 20:05.338
Hi.

20:05.438 --> 20:09.842
But then I would've had to wait
so long to give you this.

20:09.942 --> 20:10.843
What?

20:10.943 --> 20:11.844
What?

20:11.944 --> 20:13.179
Come on.

20:13.280 --> 20:14.881
You said you were
badass, right?

20:14.981 --> 20:16.516
Yeah, when I was 17.

20:16.616 --> 20:17.950
Well, that wasn't
that long ago.

20:18.050 --> 20:19.919
Uh, yeah, it is.

20:20.019 --> 20:21.288
Come on.

20:21.388 --> 20:23.723
Let's give it a go.

20:23.823 --> 20:25.725
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

20:25.825 --> 20:28.295
- Ready?
- Yes.

20:28.395 --> 20:30.463
Okay.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.499
Whoo-hoo!

20:35.468 --> 20:37.069
[laughs]

20:37.169 --> 20:38.338
Oh, snap.

